data.name: audiometry
data.description: Audiometry is an application framework written in C# and based on WPF and .NET that enables accurate digital recording, search, analysis, graphical visualization, and reproduction of human audio-vestibular impairment test data to assist in hearing loss or disability diagnosis.

name: audiometry
description: Audiometry is an application framework written in C# and based on WPF and .NET that enables accurate digital recording, search, analysis, graphical visualization, and reproduction of human audio-vestibular impairment test data to assist in hearing loss or disability diagnosis.

evidence: README mentions binaries/installers: "``Audiometry`` can be installed on a Windows 7 or Windows 10 machine. To install the application, run the AudiometryInstaller.msi in the installer folder of the repository."
"Audiometry is an open-source application framework based on WPF and .NET to create hearing test related applications."

"Audiometry can store, process, and visualize data corresponding to tuning fork tests... speech audiometry; pure-tone audiometry (PTA)... impedance audiometry; bithermal caloric test; and advanced tests..."
